replies.bodyText:
Providing cursor on Query would make it available from a pool without acquiring a connection.

I was suggesting that the proposed streaming and withCursor() methods would alter the result type once execute is eventually invoked, so it would still require a connection. Example usage might look like:
pool.createPreparedQuery(SQL)
       .withCursor()
       .execute(ar -> { 
         Cursor c = ar.result();
         // do stuff with cursor
       });
So this way execute would be the only terminal operation in the API (for executing queries). Otherwise we have 3 terminal operations (execute, cursor, and stream).

